[Nouns] credit, trust, tick, score, tally, account.
letter of credit, circular note; duplicate; mortgage, lien, debenture, paper credit, floating capital; draft, lettre de creance, securities.
creditor, lender, lessor, mortgagee; dun; usurer.
[Verbs] keep an account with, run up an account with; intrust, credit, accredit.
place to one's credit, place to one's account; give credit, take credit; fly a kite.
[Adjectives] crediting, credited; accredited.
[Adverbs] on credit; to the account of, to the credit of; a compte.
